Waits on this condition variable for a notification, timing out after a specified duration.

The semantics of this function are equivalent to [`wait`](about:blank/struct.Condvar.html#method.wait "method std::sync::Condvar::wait") except that the thread will be blocked for roughly no longer than `ms` milliseconds. This method should not be used for precise timing due to anomalies such as preemption or platform differences that might not cause the maximum amount of time waited to be precisely `ms`.

Note that the best effort is made to ensure that the time waited is measured with a monotonic clock, and not affected by the changes made to the system time.

The returned boolean is `false` only if the timeout is known to have elapsed.

Like [`wait`](about:blank/struct.Condvar.html#method.wait "method std::sync::Condvar::wait"), the lock specified will be re-acquired when this function returns, regardless of whether the timeout elapsed or not.

